
/*
 * // This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specific destination. 
 * // It retrieves nodes from two different sources using the [get-nodes] slot and adds them to the destination specified by the [add] slot's expression.
 * // 1. [add:x:./*/invoke] - This slot is used to append nodes to the destination specified by the expression.
 * // 2. [get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*] - Retrieves all nodes under the [.arguments] node.
 * // 3. [get-nodes:x:@.model/*] - Retrieves all nodes under the [.model] node.
 */
add:x:./*/invoke
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
   get-nodes:x:@.model/*
